Sentencas: Yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte membranes were surface modified by adding a 1 nm thin, high-yttria concentration YSZ film with the help of atomic layer deposition, The addition of the I nm film led to an increase of the maximum power density of a low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) by a factor of 1.50 at 400 degrees C.
Titulo: Surface Modification of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte by Atomic Layer Deposition

Sentencas: The enhanced performance can be attributed to an increased oxide ion Incorporation rate on the surface of the modified electrolyte,
Titulo: Surface Modification of Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte by Atomic Layer Deposition
